  "prompt": "Can I get infected with an STD from getting oral sex without protection?",
  "response": "Yes, it is possible to contract a sexually transmitted disease (STD) from receiving oral sex without protection. STDs that can be transmitted this way include herpes simplex virus (HSV), gonorrhea, syphilis, human papillomavirus (HPV), and, less commonly, chlamydia and HIV. It is important to use protection, such as condoms or dental dams, during oral sex to reduce the risk of transmission. If you are concerned about potential exposure to an STD, it is a good idea to speak with a healthcare provider about testing and prevention methods.",
